[10:57:30    56] +  pointer boundary and now creates the 4-byte slices only after its existing
[10:57:30    56] +  length checks.
[10:57:30    56] +- Replaced the implementation-visible `static mut global_error: error` plus
[10:57:30    56] +  raw-pointer `error` struct with non-mut atomic address/position state. Used
[10:57:30    56] +  strict-provenance `expose_provenance`/`with_exposed_provenance` APIs instead
[10:57:30    56] +  of raw pointer fields or int-to-pointer casts, and switched two parse-end
[10:57:30    56] +  calculations from unsafe `offset` to safe `wrapping_add`.
[10:57:30    56] +- Removed the unused `memset` FFI import by changing `cJSON_New_Item` to write
